        "title": "See also"
      },
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "The Weibull (or Type III asymptotic extreme value distribution\nfor smallest values, SEV Type III, or Rosin-Rammler\ndistribution) is one of a class of Generalized Extreme Value\n(GEV) distributions used in modeling extreme value problems.\nThis class includes the Gumbel and Frechet distributions."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "The probability density for the Weibull distribution is"
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "formulas": [
              "p(x) = \\frac{a} {\\lambda}(\\frac{x}{\\lambda})^{a-1}e^{-(x/\\lambda)^a},"
            ],
            "type": "math_block"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "where "
              },
              {
                "kind": "math",
                "latex": "a"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " is the shape and "
              },
              {
                "kind": "math",
                "latex": "\\lambda"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " the scale."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "The function has its peak (the mode) at\n"
              },
              {
                "kind": "math",
                "latex": "\\lambda(\\frac{a-1}{a})^{1/a}"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "When "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "a = 1"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": ", the Weibull distribution reduces to the exponential\ndistribution."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Notes"
      },
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "raw_kind": "footnote",
            "raw_text": "1\n\nWaloddi Weibull, Royal Technical University, Stockholm,\n1939 \"A Statistical Theory Of The Strength Of Materials\",\nIngeniorsvetenskapsakademiens Handlingar Nr 151, 1939,\nGeneralstabens Litografiska Anstalts Forlag, Stockholm.",
            "type": "raw_block"
          },
          {
            "raw_kind": "footnote",
            "raw_text": "2\n\nWaloddi Weibull, \"A Statistical Distribution Function of\nWide Applicability\", Journal Of Applied Mechanics ASME Paper\n1951.",
            "type": "raw_block"
          },
          {
            "raw_kind": "footnote",
            "raw_text": "3\n\nWikipedia, \"Weibull distribution\",\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Weibull_distribution",
            "type": "raw_block"
          }
        ],
        "title": "References"
      },
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "Draw samples from the distribution:"
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "lines": [
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "a = 5. # shape"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "s = fnp.random.weibull(a, 1000)"
              }
            ],
            "type": "doctest_block"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "Display the histogram of the samples, along with\nthe probability density function:"
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "lines": [
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "x = fnp.arange(1,100.)/50."
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "def weib(x,n,a):"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": "...",
                "text": "return (a / n) * (x / n)**(a - 1) * fnp.exp(-(x / n)**a)"
              }
            ],
            "type": "doctest_block"
          },
          {
            "lines": [
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "count, bins, ignored = plt.hist(fnp.random.weibull(5.,1000))"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "x = fnp.arange(1,100.)/50."
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "scale = count.max()/weib(x, 1., 5.).max()"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "plt.plot(x, weib(x, 1., 5.)*scale)"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "plt.show()"
              }
            ],
            "type": "doctest_block"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Examples"
      }
